sub_title: Partner bij NavIncerta, Consultant Economics and Applied Risk & Uncertainty Analysis
summary: Former Managing Director of Exploration and Production (EP), with many years of international experience gained on postings to several countries during a 25-year career with Shell. Broad knowledge of and experience with EP and gas activities (research, project evaluation, economics, appraisal drilling, planning, natural-gas policy, contract negotiations, team leadership and general management). Vast experience with leading people from different cultural backgrounds. Many years of experience in conducting courses on Petroleum Economics, International Petroleum Contracts and Applied Risk and Uncertainty. Received an M.Sc. for Theoretical Physics and a Ph.D. in Theoretical Nuclear Physics from the University of Groningen.
